1. Double Victory meant having both a victory overseas, against Germany and the Axis powers, and in our country, with Civil Rights.
2. He was an union leader and civil rights activist, threatening to stage a protest at the White House. Roosevelt signed E.O. 8802, which outlawed discrimination in war industries, a cause Randolph was fighing for.
3. To outlaw discrimination in war industries
4. They were being outlawed from jobs and were being segregated.
5. WWII catalized civil rights, getting African-Americans the right to work in war factories, as well as giving the Latino Civil Rights movement the confidence to proceed.
